      • PrintWriterExporter

        public PrintWriterExporter(PrintStream printStream)
        Make a new exporter that will send output to the specified stream.

        The exporter will not close the stream when it is done, or even when its close() method is invoked. Thus this constructor can be safely used on System.out and similar streams that one usually does not want to close.

        Parameters:
        printStream -

      • PrintWriterExporter

        public PrintWriterExporter()
        Make a new exporter. Should be passed a print stream at export time.
